verbs.description: unsolve (third-person singular simple present unsolves, present participle unsolving, simple past and past participle unsolved)

examples: Perchance, my Fancy would have bin so kinde, / T‘ unsolve the doubts of my perplexed minde.

entries.meaning: To undo or remove the solution to a problem; to put something into an unsolved state.
examples: “But I cannot allow you to use my cousin to solve or, I suppose, more precisely, to unsolve your case.”
